                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>No. 46 South Street</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>New York</placeName>\n                <date>October 11th 1867</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>My Dear <addressee>Mr. Leeser</addressee></p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Since I last had this pleas-<lb/>ure I have to acknowledge receipt\n                of your favor<lb/> of <date>Sept. 9th</date>\n                <del><date>August 8th</date></del> &amp; <date>7th</date> inst. together with\n                the<lb/> parcels accompanying which received due atten<lb/> tion. <persName>M.\n                    Morrison</persName>\n                <placeName>No. 3 Charles St</placeName> has retur<lb/>ned to the city and on the\n                    <date>4th</date> inst sent me<lb/> $33 which he says he thought was the\n                amt.<lb/> of your bill, (it having been mislaid) I very<lb/> politely acknowledged\n                receipt of the money<lb/> and enclosed a duplicate bill on which<lb/> I credited the\n                $33 leaving a bal of $3 still<lb/> due from this last I have as yet no\n                response.<lb/> I enclose a note from <persName>I. N. Phillips</persName>\n                (addressed<lb/> to you) with the regret that I would read<lb/> it before forwarding.\n                This note is date <date>Sept<lb/> 6th</date> but I cannot tell when it reached my\n                office<lb/> as I was absent. At all events it only came<lb/> to my hands a few days\n                since when it was<lb/> found on overhauling some loose papers<lb/> and cleaning up\n                my Desk. I regret the</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ng4h81h/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
